---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Base
  title="Attribution · QMD Search for Obsidian"
  description="Upstream projects, libraries and assets that QMD Search builds on."
  activePage="attribution"
>

<div class="wrap">
  <article class="prose">
    <div class="eyebrow">Credits</div>
    <h1>Standing on shoulders.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      QMD Search is a thin bridge over a stack of excellent upstream projects. None of them are affiliated with this plugin, and none endorse it — but it could not exist without them.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Core dependencies</h2>
      <div class="credits">
        <div class="credit">
          <div class="role">Host application</div>
          <h3>Obsidian</h3>
          <p>Knowledge-base app for plain-text Markdown vaults. QMD Search is a community plugin that registers into Obsidian's plugin API; the app itself is proprietary and is not redistributed here.</p>
          <a href="https://obsidian.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">obsidian.md →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="credit">
          <div class="role">Search engine</div>
          <h3>qmd</h3>
          <p>Local-first hybrid search engine. Provides the lexical (BM25) and semantic (vector) indexes, the embedding pipeline, and the reranker. Invoked by the plugin via its CLI.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/tobi/qmd" target="_blank" rel="noopener">qmd repository →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="credit">
          <div class="role">Distribution</div>
          <h3>BRAT</h3>
          <p>Beta Reviewer's Auto-update Tool — the Obsidian community's de facto channel for testing pre-release plugins. QMD Search is distributed through BRAT until it graduates to the official directory.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/TfTHacker/obsidian42-brat" target="_blank" rel="noopener">obsidian42-brat →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="credit">
          <div class="role">Typography</div>
          <h3>IBM Plex</h3>
          <p>Sans and Mono superfamily by IBM. Used for the documentation site (this page) and as the type reference in the plugin's UI artifacts. Open Font License.</p>
          <a href="https://www.ibm.com/plex/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ibm.com/plex →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Trademarks &amp; non-affiliation</h2>
      <p>
        Obsidian® is a trademark of Dynalist Inc. QMD Search is an independent, unofficial community plugin and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Obsidian or Dynalist Inc.
      </p>
      <p>
        The qmd name and command-line tool are property of their respective authors; this plugin merely invokes the public CLI and bundles no qmd source code.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Documentation site</h2>
      <p>
        This site is built statically with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a> and hosted on GitHub Pages. No analytics, no third-party trackers, no client-side JavaScript beyond what your browser ships natively. Fonts are loaded from Google Fonts' CDN.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>License</h2>
      <p>
        The plugin and this site are released under the <a href={`${base}/license`}>MIT License</a>. Upstream projects retain their own licenses (see links above).
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</div>

</Base>
